# PETS.CFG — the full pet roster, editable without reflashing firmware.
#
# One "PREFIX=NAME" per line.  PREFIX is the pet's sprite-prefix byte (decimal):
#   0,1,2 = the built-in pets (listing them just renames them)
#   3,4   = reserved (sponsors, menu icons) — ignored
#   5..7  = new custom pets
# NAME is up to 16 ASCII chars, shown in "Choose your Pet".
#
# A pet's sprites are the matching PPAAFF.PCX files on the badge; each
# animation part can have any number of frames — the firmware counts the
# PCX files present (050100..050104 = 5 idle frames, etc.), so no header or
# fixed frame count is needed.  Export sprites with asset-gen at the pet's
# prefix, drop them next to this file.
#
# '#' starts a comment.  Reserved / malformed rows are ignored.

# --- current pets (rename if you like) ---
0=Bartholomeus
1=Cat
2=Slug

# --- add your own (needs 05xxxx.PCX / 06xxxx.PCX sprites) ---
5=Dragon
6=Ghost
